docs.abstract: A bill backed by nearly 60 House Democrats would create a panel to develop proposals and a “national apology” to repair the lingering effects of slavery.
docs.snippet: A bill backed by nearly 60 House Democrats would create a panel to develop proposals and a “national apology” to repair the lingering effects of slavery.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — With the support of a string of 2020 Democratic presidential candidates, the idea of reparations for African-Americans is gaining traction among Democrats on Capitol Hill, where Speaker Nancy Pelosi backs the establishment of a commission that would develop proposals and a “national apology” to repair the lingering effects of slavery.

headline.main: House Democrats, With Pelosi’s Support, Will Consider a Commission on Reparations
headline.print_headline: House Democrats Consider Commission on Slavery Reparations

docs.lead_paragraph: ORLANDO, Fla. — The crowd in the Amway Center, an arena that seats 20,000, cheered loudly as oversize screens hanging from the ceiling broadcast Fox News projections that Donald J. Trump would win Florida and Ohio — in 2016.

docs.abstract: The House speaker still does not want to start an impeachment inquiry, but she ruled out censure as insufficient.
docs.snippet: The House speaker still does not want to start an impeachment inquiry, but she ruled out censure as insufficient.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — House Speaker Nancy Pelosi on Wednesday ruled out censuring President Trump as an alternative to starting an impeachment proceeding against him, and said that if Democrats conclude he should be charged under the Constitution for misconduct, impeachment was the only option.

headline.main: Pelosi Dismisses Censuring Trump: ‘If the Goods Are There, You Must Impeach’
headline.print_headline: Pelosi Rejects Suggestion For a Vote by Lawmakers To Censure the President

docs.abstract: The Supreme Court refused to hear the appeal of a man who has been held in wartime detention for 17 years with no end in sight.
docs.snippet: The Supreme Court refused to hear the appeal of a man who has been held in wartime detention for 17 years with no end in sight.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Supreme Court on Monday refused to hear a lawsuit by a Yemeni man who has been held in wartime detention for more than 17 years at the military’s Guantánamo Bay prison, prompting Justice Stephen G. Breyer to warn that the American legal system is on autopilot toward permitting life imprisonment without trial.

headline.main: Justice Breyer Raises Specter of Perpetual Detention Without Trial at Guantánamo
headline.print_headline: Justice Questions Indefinite Detention at Guantánamo

docs.abstract: An investigation at Ohio State University revealed that coaches had inklings of a team doctor’s sexual abuse. But Representative Jim Jordan’s denials are assuaging his constituents.
docs.snippet: An investigation at Ohio State University revealed that coaches had inklings of a team doctor’s sexual abuse. But Representative Jim Jordan’s denials are assuaging his constituents.
docs.lead_paragraph: URBANA, Ohio — Voters in this small town, a camera-ready county seat cut from the mold of a 1960s-era television set, believe in their congressman. Representative Jim Jordan calls this home, and his fellow Urbanans believe he is a man of integrity. They believe his family, a dynasty of wrestling icons, has served the community well.

headline.main: ‘He’s a Good Man’: Jim Jordan Finds Support at Home in Ohio State Abuse Scandal
headline.print_headline: Constituents Back Jordan After Report on the Ohio State Scandal
